manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Smolink Cat 8 Nylon Braided Ethernet Cable-Black Series Every second, even millisecond, counts in the gaming world. A good quality Ethernet cable helps you stay one step ahead of the competition.

Maximum Speed of Data Transmission Each shielding of Cat8 is made of best material. Compared with other Ethernet cable the additional shielding of Cat8 reduces the signal interference of crosstalk, noise, and other interference that degrades the signal quality. Give you THE BEST network connection and rapid data transmission ever.

Flat Ethernet Cable, Easy to Manage The flat design helps avoid tangled cords and the super flexible Cat8 Ethernet cable fit any curved surface, corner or plane. You can arrange the fiber Ethernet cable inside or along the walls or under the carpet to keep your living environment simple and pretty.
Premium Quality and Durable Quadruple shielded Cat8 with upgraded PVC protection and nylon braided jacket can withstand extreme weather yet working efficiently. It’s perfect for outdoor & indoor use.

Aluminum Anodizing Design Superior aluminum housing make the cat 8 internet cable with better heat dissipation than plastic and adds the durability of the cable. Gold-plated Connector The connectors of cable are all 50-micron gold plated,greatly improve the transmission efficiency and making the network speed faster and more stable. Protective Cap Both ends of ethernet cable are equipped with protection caps, effectively avoiding oxidation or damage before use. Triple Thickened Design Tail Special Strain Relief Support design, can bear 15000+ bending test,makes the cable joints more durable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for the money! Ethernet 50 feet cable fits perfectly for my smart TV from the modem!
reviews.reviewText: I needed a 50 feet cable to run my ethernet cable from the main living room to my bedroom. This fit the bill perfectly! Fast speed and transfer! Hope it lasts because of the value spent on it. No flaws!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this particular cable to run underneath carpet. The cable lays nice and flat and leaves no humps. The performance of the cable is stellar. Very fast transferring of data. No complaints at all with cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Network cable
reviews.reviewText: I am very impressed with the quality of these cables. I ordered 3 50ft cables and and I plan on ordering a few more shorter ones soon. The price is great for the quality of the cables. I highly recommend this cable to anyone that needs a patch cable of any length. I usually run my own cables and crimp on the ends but I don't bother anymore unless I need a very long run. Plus, these are Cat 8 which maybe overkill but why not for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really well made...
reviews.reviewText: Great quality cables at a great price...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value for the price
reviews.reviewText: Very nice cable, well made, good value for the price, time will only tell if it's going to survive the outdoor or not

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid cable, works fine for what I need
reviews.reviewText: This preforms as expected and was probably the best deal on a Cat 8 at the time I looked. I would definitely buy one again. The one little thing I didn't like was that the cord came tightly coiled and had a small, but harmless, kink in the center. This was easy to straighten out but I wish they could coil it slightly looser and not have to do that. Regardless, it's a solid product as far as I can tell.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reduced RF interference
reviews.reviewText: It works! Previously, I used a 50ft Cat 6 cable, but my LAN speed fluctuated and sometimes dropped entirely. From YT, one commenter mentioned LAN speed could fluctuate due to RF interference. Shielded cable is a solution. Cat 8 cables are by default shielded, so I tried this. Problem solved. My LAN speed is now constantly high, as it should be.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these braided cables! Wish I could confirm they are genuine CAT 8
reviews.reviewText: I really like these cables. They look good, they are easier to maneuver without getting tangled up and they snap in the ports well. Thinking of replacing ALL my cables with these. I would just like to confirm that they are genuine CAT 8 cables. Can anyone with an ethernet cable tester confirm this?

Rest assured this is a high quality CAT8 cable.However, would a normal home user benefit from it? Sadly, it’s a resulting No.Didn’t see any difference in fibre broadband speed when comparing between CAT6 and CAT8 cable.The true benefit of this cable can only be noticed for those fibre speeds ranging between 25Gbps to 40Gbps at a short range of 30m. So it’s fair to say, this cable is more beneficial for servers in Data Centre environments.
